<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,326,568]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,326,352]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described based on a single female from 
<collectingCountry box="[957,1025,326,352]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1043,1217,326,352]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
). After the original description and redescription by 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[518,718,362,388]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" pagination="209 - 335" refId="ref4683" refString="Breuning, S. (1971 a) Revision des especes americaines de la tribue des Apomecynini Lac. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen aus dem Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde, 37 (3), 209 - 335." type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning (1971a)</bibRefCitation>
, the species has only been mentioned in catalogs and checklists. Based on the short distance between the upper eye lobes, probably it is not a true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[1074,1163,398,424]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1074,1163,398,424]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Bisaltes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Interestingly, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." pageId="7" pageNumber="102" pagination="265 - 274" refId="ref4618" refString="Breuning, S. (1950) Quelques nouveaux Lamiaires (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) du Riksmuseum. Arkiv for Zoologi, Series 2, 1, 265 - 274." type="journal article" year="1950">Breuning (1950</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[230,299,434,460]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" pagination="209 - 335" refId="ref4683" refString="Breuning, S. (1971 a) Revision des especes americaines de la tribue des Apomecynini Lac. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen aus dem Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde, 37 (3), 209 - 335." type="journal article" year="1971">1971a</bibRefCitation>
) did not mention anything about the distance between the upper eye lobes. Unfortunately, we were not able to identify the genus and/or tribe using the photograph at our disposal. Therefore, the species is provisionally retained in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[277,366,506,532]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[277,366,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Bisaltes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is important to note that southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[826,894,506,532]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Brazil</collectingCountry>
is an area where extensive specimen collections have taken place and apparently, no other specimens of this species have been collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
